About me

Presently, I am a Ph.D. student working under the supervision of Dr. Sohom Ray, at the Department of Earthquake Engineering, IIT Roorkee. My research focuses on developing data-driven algorithms to identify underlying governing equations of physical dynamics such as basal slip development, and earthquake nucleation for landslide problems.

Projects

Internship Project 5th July, 2019

”Generation of dispersion curve for Andaman Region by forward modeling”

  • Used forward modelling code to obtain Rayleigh wave dispersion curve.

  • Calculated sensitivity and obtained the maximum sensitivity period range.

Coursework Project 27th November, 2020

”Application of Digital Wiener Filtering in Seismic Data Processing” : Designed Wiener filter for spiking deconvolution and predictive deconvolution. Worked in Matlab programming environment.

Dissertation Project 22th April, 2021

”A Strategy Towards Modeling Subduction Zone” : Analysed datasets to characterise and obtain geometry of subduction zone. Modelled deformation pattern variation with depth along Sunda Subduction Zone.
